Introduction

SUPER JUNIOR-T (Korean: 슈퍼주니어-트; Japanese: スーパージュニア-T), also known as Super Junior-Trot, is the second official sub-unit of the boy group Super Junior under Label SJ, a subsidary of SM Entertainment.
They are the first idol group known for capitalizing trot music, one of the oldest forms of Korean pop music. The unit debuted on February 23, 2007 but were announced to be on hiatus in December 2008.
The unit consists of members; Leeteuk, Heechul, Shindong, Sungmin, and Eunhyuk.
